javax.constraints
Interface VarReal

All Superinterfaces:
ConstrainedVariable
public interface VarReal
extends ConstrainedVariable

This interface represents constrained real variables.

setMax

void setMax(double max)
            throws java.lang.Exception
Sets a new maximum for the domain of this variable. If 'max' is more than the current maximum, it throws an exception. This method should be implemented by a concrete CP solver implementation.

Parameters:
max - the new maximum value for this variable.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - if the new maximum is not in the domain of this variable.

setMin

Throws:
java.lang.Exception - if the new minimum is not in the domain of this variable.

setValue

void setValue(double value)
              throws java.lang.Exception

Parameters:

Throws:
java.lang.Exception - if the given value is not in the domain of this variable.
